    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>I don't know anything about Codeigniter specifically but I don't think it's necessary to break it off into separate read/write classes.  In fact, in this instance that might actually be <em>bad</em> practice because in OOP a model is supposed to represent a single entity.  You should google DAL (Database Abstraction Layer). If have a Widgets model then it's perfectly ok to have both getters and setters.  My point is that it may not be the <em>best</em> practice in your case just to simply break off into smaller classes.  This should always be purpose-driven.</p>
    </div>
